 planning for future financial endeavors for long term budget planning 40 dissemination of cepa research the associate director will be responsible for outreach and dissemination of information about the activities and research of cepa to a wide variety of audiences including academics policy makers and media to ensure the continuing growth of cepa develop written content for the website and materials needed for cepa events help in designing a dissemination plan for cepa's research and work that may include newsletters mass mailings etc 20 other development activities including strategic and event planning to grow and contribute to the development of the center qualifications the successful candidate will have a doctorate in education policy or a related field economics sociology or political science while the associate director will not conduct research he she will facilitate the research of cepa faculty staff and students on several fronts accordingly the candidate must understand the types of data and quantitative research methods typically used for policy analysis and he she should have experience with grant writing and other methods of securing funding for academic research centers the associate director will also help direct the business operations of cepa which will require strong managerial skills these include excellent written and oral communication skills as well as analytical organizational and problem solving skills and an ability to work with and direct others requires 1 2 years relevant experience 2 3 years preferred this is a fixed term position with an end date of 03 01 2014 apply at https jobs stanford edu about us about cepa mission news resources career opportunities contact center for education policy analysis stanford university 520 galvez mall ceras building 5th floor stanford ca 94305 3084 phone 650 736 1258 fax 650 723 9931 terms of use copyright complaints cepa webmaster
